1�Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya?You got nothin' on me, ?[man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
1�Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky!Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
1�Do you want to hear a story?No, thank you.Let's hear one.

1�I knew our undying faith would show us the way,  . Yes, Altana's righteous light is strong enough to pierce even the thickest of subterranean stones.
1�Oh my...With so many beady eyes and toothy grins, how are we ever to tell which belong to the Velkk we met earlier?
1�Aha, it is easier than I thought when we have witches to direct us!
1�Feast your eyes upon the one who can barely keep from drooling on himself! That's Mligni-Vorgut, Gramk-Droog's new prodigy.
1�Ugh, Altana truly works in mysterious ways...I was hoping to blast these creatures back to the Great Expedition with some sorcery, but I can't with him here.
1�We have to find a way to separate the Velkk we need from Mligni-Vorgut and his cascade of sputum...
1�Do you think you could...uh...thin the herd a bit? I think I might be able to bag the bulb if there were fewer eyes watching.

1�Hmmm...I think 
� should do the trick...though a few more certainly couldn't hurt.
1�My apologies that I am unable to craft a more foolproof plan, but I was not blessed with the brightest of minds. Best of luck,  !

1�You will need to slay 
� of the Velkk that dirty this area so I can sneak in and take back the bulb...for the greater good!
1�My apologies that I am unable to craft a more foolproof plan, but I was not blessed with the brightest of minds. Best of luck,  !
1�Y-you mean to say I simply appeared out of thin air?
1�Well, if you have not the foggiest idea how I was transported, that must mean...it was the witch?
1�I could ask the same of you, Araustoix.
1�Please, do not blame  ! I coerced ?[him/her] into coming with my grandiloquent talk of justice and duty. ?[He/She] has done nothing wrong!
1� , you have been more than kind putting up with my absurd requests, and for that I am eternally in your debt.
1�Please accept this as compensation for your troubles.
1�Thanks to your valiant efforts, we have seized the coven's potentially life-threatening bulb, and our city is safe for the time being.
1�And yet that black-hearted Mithra took it upon herself to save me from certain death...
1�Well, I best get back and face the music. Fare thee well,  , and may we meet again soon!
1�Hey, don't leave me out to drrry. I love a good slaughterfest.
1�Me take care them. Me gouge them good. Innards run splickity-splat on ground.
1�Nashu? What on the Goddess's green earth are you doing here?
1�I am here on official business from the priory, unlike you, who are disobeying orders by being here. We specifically told you to leave everything in our more capable hands.
1�That goes for you as well. Just because you have delved into these depths before does not make them any less dangerous.
1�For the heavens' sake, have you no shame, Nashu? Bringing a pioneer along on an assuredly dangerous endeavor... No wonder you have yet to become a full-fledged exorcist.
1�However, I must say that I did not expect the rumors to be true.
1�My stomach contents curdle at the thought of people from the same races as we Adoulinians aiding the despicable Velkk. I must notify Lord Vortimere at once.
1�Nashu, you are to return with me as well. We can decide on a punishment befitting your impudence at a later date.
1�A bittersweet breeze of melancholy and remembrance graces the air about you for one fleeting moment.
1�...No. Let them come. I will carry out my charge for as long as I draw brrreath.
1�And the word of a geomancer is sacrrred!
